TextEng: You seem rather nervous. What's your name?
Text: 꽤 긴장한 것 같은데. 이름이 뭐지?

TextEng: I don't look like who?
Who you be?
Me not look like who?
I am <FirstName>. What creatures are you talking about?
My name is <FullName> and I am interested in hearing more about these creatures.
Text: 내 이름은 <FullName>이고, 그 생명체에 대해 더 듣고 싶은데.

TextEng: Nevermind my name, what are these creatures you are looking for?
Text: 이름은 신경 쓰지 마. 네가 찾고 있는 게 뭔데?

TextEng: Me be <FirstName>. What creatures you hunt?
Me name be <FullName> and me want know more about creatures.
Text: 나 이름 <FullName>이고 생명체 더 알고 싶어.

TextEng: You not need know name. You tell me about creatures.
Maybe we should start with introductions.
Trolls? Tell me more!
Trolls. You tell me 'bout trolls.
So you are looking for dead things?
Text: 그래서 죽은 것들을 찾고 있다는 거야?

TextEng: You mean you want find dead thing?
Trolls? Ogres? Tell me more about them.
Text: 트롤? 오우거? 그것들에 대해 더 말해봐.

TextEng: Tell me more about this creator race.
Text: 그 창조자 종족에 대해 더 말해줘.

TextEng: What kind of treasure are you suggesting?
I think I've heard enough. Goodbye.
Text: 이제 충분히 들은 것 같네. 잘 가.

TextEng: Me want know about trolls.
What more you know about creator race?
Treasure? Me want hear more 'bout treasure.
Text: 보물? 나 보물 더 듣고 싶어.

TextEng: Me grow bored. Bye bye.
What you need for to prove?
I could help you look for this ancient tome.
Text: 그 고대의 책을 찾는 걸 도와줄 수 있어.

TextEng: I'm not really interested.
I help you get tome.
Me not care for books. Me find other things to do.
Text: 나 책 안 좋아해. 다른 거 할래.

TextEng: What were you looking for again?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I want to help you find that book. How much will you pay me?
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 책 찾는 걸 돕고 싶은데. 얼마나 줄 건데?

TextEng: This wouldn't happen to be the book you are looking for, would it?
Text: 혹시 네가 찾던 책이 이거 아닐까?

TextEng: You say what you looking for again?
Me want look for book. How much you pay?
Text: 나 책 찾고 싶어. 얼마 줘?

TextEng: Maybe this be book you want?
Goodbye.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> You wouldn't believe the hell I had to go through to get this. Surely you could afford a little more.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 이거 구하느라 얼마나 고생했는지 모를 거야. 분명 좀 더 줄 수 있을 텐데.

TextEng: You better fork over more than that or you'll get to experience all the pain I suffered recovering the darn thing.
Text: 더 안 주면 내가 이거 구하느라 겪은 고통을 네가 똑같이 겪게 해주지.

TextEng: Certainly, that sounds fine by me.
Not a chance. Finders keepers you know.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Me work hard to find. Me want more.
Me show you how much it hurt to find 'less you give me more!
Text: 더 안 주면 내가 얼마나 아팠는지 보여줄 거야!

TextEng: That seem fair.
No selling! Me keeping book. Finders keepers.
Text: 안 팔아! 나 가질 거야. 주운 사람이 임자야.

TextEng: All right. 750 gold pieces it is.
Okay. 750 gp.
I don't think so. I can get a better price from someone else, I think.
Text: 안 될 것 같은데. 다른 사람한테 더 받을 수 있을 것 같아.

TextEng: Nope, me sell for more to someone else.
Text: 안 돼. 다른 사람한테 더 받고 팔 거야.

TextEng: That sounds better. Hand over the gold.
Nope, I'm keeping it.
That be better. Here you book.
Nope, me keep.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> All right. I hate to part with it for only 500 gp, though...
I guess I need the 500 gold more than the book.
Text: 책보다 금화 500이 더 필요할 것 같네.

TextEng: That's all right. I can find someone else who will pay me for it, I think.
Text: 괜찮아. 더 쳐주는 다른 사람을 찾을 수 있을 거야.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Mmmm... okay. But me likes it a lot... 500 gold pieces seems not so much.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 으음... 좋아. 하지만 나 이거 좋아하는데... 금화 500 너무 적어.

TextEng: Me guesses 500 gold pieces is okay.
Nope. Me sell someone else for more.
Text: 안 돼. 다른 사람한테 더 받고 팔 거야.

TextEng: Where did you say you thought that book was?
I think I found your book, is this it?
Text: 네 책 찾은 것 같은데, 이거 맞아?

TextEng: No, nothing yet.
Quit being so pushy! I'll get around to finding it.
Found it, me thinks. This it?
Nope. But me working on it.
You no bug me. Me find when good and ready to find.
Where me find book again?
Okay, goodbye.
What did you do then?
Obviously you didn't hire good guards!
I'm sorry for your grief.
Get to the point.
Me sorry they die.
Hurry up.
What you do?
Why you no hire big, strong guards?
Text: 왜 크고 강한 경비병 안 고용했어?

TextEng: When did they fight dragons?
How long ago did this supposedly take place?
When fight dragons?
When this maybe happen?
And you think you can prove this race existed?
Text: 그래서 그 종족이 존재했다는 걸 증명할 수 있다는 거야?

TextEng: Grant money? Is that what you are worried about?
What is the grant money for?
Text: 연구 보조금은 뭐 하는 데 쓰는 건데?

TextEng: What grant money?
Ah! You care 'bout money. That me understand.
Text: 아! 돈 걱정하는구나. 그건 나도 알아.

TextEng: That would be just fine.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> This sounds very dangerous. I think some money up front would be justified.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 꽤 위험해 보이는데. 선금 좀 받는 게 당연하지 않을까.

TextEng: That be good.
All right, I'm off.
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> This sound dangerous. Me want gold first to do job.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 위험해 보여. 일 시작하기 전에 돈 줘.

TextEng: Me off.
Good enough, for now.
Me agree, for now.
What's your name again?
What you called?
What kind of research do you do here?
What re-search? What you do here?
Research? You mean you're hunting creatures?
Uhh... you mean you hunts stuff?
